3/15/17, 8:54 PM - Juan D. RodrÃ­guez: AAAAY
3/15/17, 8:54 PM - Juan D. RodrÃ­guez: tienes por ahÃ­ el arduino?
3/15/17, 8:54 PM - Juan D. RodrÃ­guez: para que veas algo
3/15/17, 8:54 PM - Juan D. RodrÃ­guez: jajajaja
3/15/17, 8:54 PM - Juan D. RodrÃ­guez: /*
 Fade

 This example shows how to fade an LED on pin 9
 using the analogWrite() function.

 The analogWrite() function uses PWM, so if
 you want to change the pin you're using, be
 sure to use another PWM capable pin. On most
 Arduino, the PWM pins are identified with 
 a "~" sign, like ~3, ~5, ~6, ~9, ~10 and ~11.

 This example code is in the public domain.
 */

int led = 9;           // the PWM pin the LED is attached to
int brightness = 0;    // how bright the LED is
int fadeAmount = 5;    // how many points to fade the LED by

// the setup routine runs once when you press reset:
void setup() {
  // declare pin 9 to be an output:
  pinMode(led, OUTPUT);
}

// the loop routine runs over and over again forever:
void loop() {
  // set the brightness of pin 9:
  analogWrite(led, brightness);

  // change the brightness for next time through the loop:
  brightness = brightness + fadeAmount;

  // reverse the direction of the fading at the ends of the fade:
  if (brightness <= 0 || brightness >= 255) {
    fadeAmount = -fadeAmount;
  }
  // wait for 30 milliseconds to see the dimming effect
  delay(30);
}

4/10/17, 11:55 AM - Juan D. RodrÃ­guez: #define rfTransmitPin 4  //RF Transmitter pin = digital pin 4
boolean value = false;

void setup(){
   pinMode(rfTransmitPin, OUTPUT);
   Serial.begin(9600);
 }
 
 void loop(){
 digitalWrite(rfTransmitPin, (value = !value)? HIGH : LOW); 
   delay(50);
 }

4/10/17, 1:38 PM - Juan D. RodrÃ­guez: #include <RH_ASK.h>
#include <SPI.h> // Not actually used but needed to compile

RH_ASK driver;

void setup()
{
    Serial.begin(9600);   // Debugging only
    if (!driver.init())
         Serial.println("init failed");
}

void loop()
{
    const char *msg = "Hello World!";
    driver.send((uint8_t *)msg, strlen(msg));
    driver.waitPacketSent();
    delay(1000);
}

4/10/17, 4:49 PM - Jà¦¢â€Œâ€Œâ€Œâ€Œà§­à§¸ Aà§¸à¦ à¦£à§à§§: -_

4/10/17, 4:49 PM - Juan D. RodrÃ­guez: /*
* Ultrasonic Sensor HC-SR04 and Arduino Tutorial
*
* Crated by Dejan Nedelkovski,
* www.HowToMechatronics.com
*
*/
// defines pins numbers
const int trigPin = 7;
const int echoPin = 6;
// defines variables
long duration;
int distance;
void setup() {
pinMode(trigPin, OUTPUT); // Sets the trigPin as an Output
pinMode(echoPin, INPUT); // Sets the echoPin as an Input
Serial.begin(9600); // Starts the serial communication
}
void loop() {
// Clears the trigPin
digitalWrite(trigPin, LOW);
delayMicroseconds(2);
// Sets the trigPin on HIGH state for 10 micro seconds
digitalWrite(trigPin, HIGH);
delayMicroseconds(10);
digitalWrite(trigPin, LOW);
// Reads the echoPin, returns the sound wave travel time in microseconds
duration = pulseIn(echoPin, HIGH);
// Calculating the distance
distance= duration*0.034/2;
// Prints the distance on the Serial Monitor
Serial.print("Distance: ");
Serial.print(distance);
Serial.print("    Time: ");
Serial.println(duration);
}

4/11/17, 12:16 PM - Jà¦¢â€Œâ€Œâ€Œâ€Œà§­à§¸ Aà§¸à¦ à¦£à§à§§: Me gusta Tous Les MÃªmes de Stromae".
4/11/17, 5:50 PM - Jà¦¢â€Œâ€Œâ€Œâ€Œà§­à§¸ Aà§¸à¦ à¦£à§à§§: /*
* 
* Si la distancia estÃ¡ entre paredMin y paredMax, se toma como un "vacÃ­o".
* Si la distancia es menor a paredMin, se toma como si hubiera un auto ahÃ­.
* Las variables paredMin y paredMax son nÃºmeros enteros en cm.
* 
* Por RF se mandan los datos de cuÃ¡l sensor de ultrasonido estÃ¡ captando
* una distancia menor a la establecida (0, 1, 2 Ã³ 1 y 2)
* 
* driver.send("--3--", 5);
* driver.send("(mensaje a enviar)", (tamaÃ±o del mensaje a enviar));
*/
#include <RH_ASK.h>
#include <SPI.h> // Not actually used but needed to compile
RH_ASK driver;

// defines pins numbers
const int trigPin[] = {7, 5};
const int echoPin[] = {6, 4};
// defines variables
int distance[] = {0, 0};

const int paredMin = 10;
const int paredMax = 15;

void setup() {
  pinMode(trigPin[1], OUTPUT); // Sets the trigPin1 as an Output
  pinMode(trigPin[0], OUTPUT); // Sets the trigPin2 as an Output
  pinMode(echoPin[1], INPUT); // Sets the echoPin1 as an Input
  pinMode(echoPin[0], INPUT); // Sets the echoPin2 as an Input
  Serial.begin(9600); // Starts the serial communication
  if (!driver.init())
         Serial.println("init failed");
}
void loop() {
  distance[0] = getDistance(0);
  distance[1] = getDistance(1);
  if (distance[0]>paredMax || distance[0]<0){
    distance[0] = paredMax+1;
  }
  if (distance[1]<0 || distance[1]>paredMax){
    distance[1] = paredMax+1;
  }
  
  if (distance[0]<paredMin && distance[1]<paredMin){
    driver.send("--3--", 5);
    driver.waitPacketSent();
    Serial.print("Distance 1: ");
    Serial.print(distance[0]);
    Serial.print("     |    ");
    Serial.print("Distance 2: ");
    Serial.print(distance[1]);
    Serial.println("      <-- 3");
  }
  else if (distance[0]<paredMin && distance[1]>=paredMin){
    driver.send("--1--", 5);
    driver.waitPacketSent();
    Serial.print("Distance 1: ");
    Serial.print(distance[0]);
    Serial.print("     |    ");
    Serial.print("Distance 2: ");
    Serial.print(distance[1]);
    Serial.println("     <-- 1");
  }
  else if (distance[0]>=paredMin && distance[1]>=paredMin){
    driver.send("--0--", 5);
    driver.waitPacketSent();
    Serial.print("Distance 1: ");
    Serial.print(distance[0]);
    Serial.print("    |    ");
    Serial.print("Distance 2: ");
    Serial.print(distance[1]);
    Serial.println("     -");
  }
  else if (distance[0]>=paredMin && distance[1]<paredMin){
    driver.send("--2--", 5);
    driver.waitPacketSent();
    Serial.print("Distance 1: ");
    Serial.print(distance[0]);
    Serial.print("    |    ");
    Serial.print("Distance 2: ");
    Serial.print(distance[1]);
    Serial.println("      <-- 2");
  }
}

int getDistance(int id){
  int distance, duration;
// Clears the trigPin
  digitalWrite(trigPin[id], LOW);
  delayMicroseconds(1);
  // Sets the trigPin on HIGH state for 10 micro seconds
  digitalWrite(trigPin[id], HIGH);
  delayMicroseconds(2);
  digitalWrite(trigPin[id], LOW);
  // Reads the echoPin, returns the sound wave travel time in microseconds
  duration = pulseIn(echoPin[id], HIGH);
  // Calculating the distance
  distance= duration*0.0343/2;
  return distance;
}

const byte trigPin = 7, echoPin = 6;
const int paredMin = 6, paredMax = 10;
int distance = 0;
int carro[] = {0, 0, 0};
int sensor[] = {0, 0, 0};
int sensorPast[] = {0,0,0},
    sensorPast2[] = {0,0,0},
    sensorPast3[] = {0,0,0};

void setup(){
   pinMode(trigPin, OUTPUT); // Sets the trigPin as an Output
   pinMode(echoPin, INPUT); // Sets the echoPin as an Input
  
    Serial.begin(9600); // Debugging only
    if (!driver.init()) Serial.println("init failed");
}

void loop(){
  distance = getDistance();
  String temp = "";
  
  if (distance > paredMax || distance < 0) distance = paredMax + 1;
  
  if (distance < paredMin) temp = "1";
  else if (distance >= paredMin) temp = "0";
  
    uint8_t buf[40];
    uint8_t buflen = sizeof(buf);
    if(driver.recv(buf, &buflen)){//captures the message, within the initial and final data frames
      int init, final;//used to determine initial and end points from the message received
      String message = (char*)buf;//buffer chars received saved into string for processing
      init = message.indexOf("--") + 2;
      final = message.indexOf("--", init - 1);
      message = message.substring(init, final);//saves the truly important data from the message
      int val = message.toInt();
      for(int i = 0; i < 2; i++) sensor[i] = val == i + 1 || val == 3? 1 : 0;
      sensor[2] = temp.toInt();
      
      for(int i = 0; i < 3; i++){
        if(sensorPast3[i] == 0 && sensorPast2[i] == 0 && sensorPast[i] == 0 && sensor[i] == 1) carro[i]++;
        sensorPast3[i] = sensorPast2[i];
        sensorPast2[i] = sensorPast[i];
        sensorPast[i] = sensor[i];
      }
      
      Serial.print("Sensores: {");
      Serial.print(sensor[0]);
      Serial.print(", ");
      Serial.print(sensor[1]);
      Serial.print(", ");
      Serial.print(sensor[2]);
      
      Serial.print("}    ||    ");
      
      Serial.print("Carros: {");
      Serial.print(carro[0]);
      Serial.print(", ");
      Serial.print(carro[1]);
      Serial.print(", ");
      Serial.print(carro[2]);
      Serial.println("}");
    }
}

int getDistance(){
  int distance, duration;
// Clears the trigPin
  digitalWrite(trigPin, LOW);
  delayMicroseconds(1);
  // Sets the trigPin on HIGH state for 10 micro seconds
  digitalWrite(trigPin, HIGH);
  delayMicroseconds(10);
  digitalWrite(trigPin, LOW);
  // Reads the echoPin, returns the sound wave travel time in microseconds
  duration = pulseIn(echoPin, HIGH);
  
  return duration*0.0343/2;
}
